        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "aspnet_Membership_UnlockUser",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to unlock a user account in an ASP.NET membership database. It resets the lockout status and failed login attempt counters for a specified user within a given application. This procedure is typically used in scenarios where a user has been locked out due to too many failed login attempts, and an administrator needs to manually unlock the account."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
